Italy, Belgium and Austria have met well over record-high hourly portions of variable renewable energy (VRE) in contrast to last year, achieving nearly 63%, 67% and 70% instantaneous VRE, respectively (see Fig. 4
                     ). However, Germany had also a new record low in consequence of declining demand. Inversely, California and Texas have experience of VRE shares similar to last year (see Fig. 4e and 4f). These states experienced further hourly VRE shares before lockdown measures, demonstrating that in some cases variability as a result of climate change had more powerful impacts than reductions in electricity demand owing to COVID-19 (Source data used in Fig. 4 
                     [52]).
